sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: T18 domain
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: T18 domain of CyaA from Bordetella pertussis
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for the T18 domain of the adenylate cyclase, CyaA, from Bordetella pertussis. When associated with the T25 domain of CyaA, the two domains together become active and catalyzes the conversion of ATP to cAMP.
